<p style="text-align:justify;"><a href="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg" target="_blank"><img data-attachment-id="12016" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2016/11/19/moving-on/image3-2/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,900" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="image3" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-12016" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" alt="image3" width="474" height="356" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg?w=474&amp;h=356 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg?w=948&amp;h=712 948w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image3.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">This has been a tough year. Mum&#8217;s illness and death has really taken its toll, but we have to move on. Just after mum died, I took delivery of a camper van. This is a totally new experience for me as I&#8217;ve never owned one before. Mark of <a href="https://markswalkingblog.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">Mark&#8217;s walking blog</a> owns a <a href="http://wellhouseleisure.com/alphard/" target="_blank">Wellhouse Leisure Toyota Alphard</a> and recommended it.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">After doing a bit of research, the Alphard looked extremely good value. It&#8217;s about half the price of similarly specced vehicles like VW T5/6&#8217;s. Although it&#8217;s a very high quality conversion, the reason it&#8217;s such good value is that Wellhouse use imported second-hand Toyota Alphard&#8217;s from Japan that are over ten years old.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Despite the age, they are in very good condition and have a high spec, although without many of the many modern fripperies like a trip computer. The actual basis of the vehicle is similar to a Lexus RX300. They are either 2WD or 4WD and have either a 2.4L or a 3.0L V6 engine. I was really lucky to pick up a 4WD 3.0L V6 with low mileage (57,000, 2002 registration).</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><a href="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg" target="_blank"><img data-attachment-id="12017" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2016/11/19/moving-on/image1-2/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,900" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="image1" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-12017" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" alt="image1" width="474" height="356" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg?w=474&amp;h=356 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg?w=948&amp;h=712 948w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image1.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a>Wellhouse Leisure were great to deal with, especially for a neophyte like me. Once I&#8217;d selected my base model, I added some extras: leather seats, Cat1 alarm &amp; immobilser, double din stereo, lagged/heated water tanks, bike rack, cruise control and solar panel. Total cost was Â£24,050.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">I&#8217;ve never driven a vehicle larger than a car, so driving back from Wellhouse&#8217;s premises near Huddersfield was a little nerve-wracking. However, I soon got used to the high driving position and different controls. The V6 engine is a real boon as it has plenty of power and decent acceleration for a large vehicle.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">My only criticism is that it only has a four-speed automatic gearbox (Toyota didn&#8217;t fit five-speed until 2005). For motorway cruising, it revs higher than I&#8217;m used to. However, it&#8217;s nice and relaxing to drive , even at higher speeds.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><a href="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg" target="_blank"><img data-attachment-id="12020" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2016/11/19/moving-on/image2-3/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,900" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="image2" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-12020" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" alt="image2" width="474" height="356" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg?w=474&amp;h=356 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg?w=948&amp;h=712 948w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/image2.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">So far I&#8217;ve taken it on one trip. My mum&#8217;s funeral coincided with our daughter&#8217;s reading week break from university. Instead of taking the train back to Manchester, I drove her up and then spent a couple of days in the Lake District, staying at Braithwaite camp site.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Compared with staying in a tent, it&#8217;s luxurious, especially in cold weather (it&#8217;s got a heater than runs off the petrol tank). On the middle night I camped out on the fells, but the next morning the weather turned unsettled with sleety showers so I went back to the van and spent a lazy day. The next day, I decided to go home. It was wonderful not to have a wet tent to pack.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">I&#8217;m still on a learning curve and have needed to buy a few bits and pieces. For the colder months, it&#8217;s fabulous. It opens up new opportunities. I&#8217;ll be off again mid-December for a couple of days before collecting our daughter again from university. I&#8217;ll probably just do a couple of day walks this time.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Some more pictures of the Alphard from the <a href="http://wellhouseleisure.com/alphard/?portfolio3_categories=toyota-gallery" target="_blank">Wellhouse website</a></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Mark is selling his Alphard because he wants a larger vehicle. If you&#8217;re interested he&#8217;s advertised it on preloved<a href="http://www.preloved.co.uk/adverts/show/115856409/toyota-alphard-camper-van.html?link=%2Fsearch%3Fkeyword%3Dalphard" target="_blank"> here </a></p>
